A MAN died after his car crashed into a steel structure on the side of the road. The incident reportedly happened in Kempton Park, Ekurhuleni, on Sunday 27 February on the R21’s Pomona Road. According to Emer-G-Med, paramedics responded to the scene of a horrific motor car crash on the R21, Southbound near the Pomona off-ramp. “On arrival on the scene, a Mercedes-Benz was found to have left the roadway, smashing into a steel structure at high speed and impact,” Emer-G-Med said.  Upon closer inspection, paramedics found a man believed to be roughly 40 years old, severely entrapped in the wreckage.  The man was found to have sustained fatal injuries and there was nothing paramedics could do to help him. He was declared dead on the scene.